{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872442589,"sessionID":"ses_285c15d52ffepfa12E8jzO5MFc","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3efc87001F8TMf031WzteDg","messageID":"msg_d7a3eea36001GGZPdemjFg9XTl","sessionID":"ses_285c15d52ffepfa12E8jzO5MFc","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1b6643e51aa147c7b810e7d2290d7f6d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cli-toolkit/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cli-toolkit/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n4: \n5: ## Package layout (every module path and role)\n6: \n7: | Path | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `pyproject.toml` | Project metadata, dependencies, console script mapping |\n10: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Package version `__version__`, exports `app`, runtimes |\n11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n12: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `app`, all commands, `_handle_error`, `version_callback` |\n13: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n14: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Re-exports runtimes + `MetadataOptions` |\n15: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` |\n16: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | `BuildRuntime` |\n17: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` |\n18: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` |\n19: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` |\n20: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package docstring |\n21: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `AgentMetadata`, `MetadataService` |\n22: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | `DockerService` |\n23: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` |\n24: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` |\n25: | `agentcube/operations/__init__.py` | Placeholder module docstring (no symbols) |\n26: | `examples/hello-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n27: | `examples/math-agent/main.py` | Example agent |\n28: \n29: **Setuptools packages** (from `pyproject.toml` `[tool.setuptools]`):  \n30: `agentcube`, `agentcube.cli`, `agentcube.runtime`, `agentcube.operations`, `agentcube.services`  \n31: *(Note: `agentcube.models` is not listed in `[tool.setuptools] packages` but is imported; packaging may rely on setuptools discovery for subpackages — reconstruct imports from source as above.)*\n32: \n33: ## Console script entry point\n34: \n35: ```toml\n36: [project.scripts]\n37: kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n38: ```\n39: \n40: Typer app object: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n41: \n42: ## Typer — root callback\n43: \n44: ```python\n45: def main(\n46:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n47:         None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\",\n48:         callback=version_callback, is_eager=True,\n49:     ),\n50:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n51: ) -> None:\n52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ## Typer — `pack`\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: def pack(\n59:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n60:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name\"),\n61:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java)\"),\n62:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command\"),\n63:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile\"),\n64:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud\"),\n65:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n66:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace\"),\n67:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n68: ) -> None:\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## Typer — `build`\n72: \n73: ```python\n74: def build(\n75:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n76:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n77:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n78:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n79:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n80: ) -> None:\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ## Typer — `publish`\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: def publish(\n87:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n88:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n89:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n90:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n91:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n92:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n93:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n94:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n95:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n96:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n97:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n98:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n99:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n100: ) -> None:\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ## Typer — `invoke`\n104: \n105: ```python\n106: def invoke(\n107:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n108:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n109:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n110:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n111:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n112: ) -> None:\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ## Typer — `status`\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: def status(\n119:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n120:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n121:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n122: ) -> None:\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ## Helper functions (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n126: \n127: ```python\n128: def version_callback(value: bool) -> None: ...\n129: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None: ...  # prints, typer.Exit(1)\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ## Runtime classes\n133: \n134: ### `PackRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n135: \n136: ```python\n137: class PackRuntime:\n138:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n139:     def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n140:     def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n141:     def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n142:     def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n143:     def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n144:     def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n145:     def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n146:     def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n147:     def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n148:     def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n149:     def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n150:     def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n151:     def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n152:     def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n153:     def 